My time to shine. OVER(PARTITION BY...

SELECT * FROM (SELECT *, DENSE_RANK() OVER (PARTITION BY department ORDER BY salary DESC) AS rank FROM employees) ranked WHERE rank <= 3;

DENSE_RANK handles ties correctly. If two people tie for 2nd, they both get rank 2 and the next person gets rank 3. ROW_NUMBER would arbitrarily break the tie. Chapter 7 of The Window to the Soul covers this exact scenario.

